diff_user.user:
An incorrect diff format was detected in this change:
Here's an improvement focusing on handling the 'country' and 'capital' predicates more gracefully to create more natural sentences, especially when multiple location-based triples are present:

```diff
<<<<<<< SEARCH
            elif predicate == "country":
                country_obj = object_
                properties.append(f"is in {country_obj}")
            elif predicate == "capital":
                if "is in" in properties:
                    country_index = properties.index(f"is in {country_obj}")
                    properties[country_index] = f"is in {country_obj}, where the capital is {object_}."
                else:
                    properties.append(f"has a capital of {object_}")
>>>>>>> REPLACE
            elif predicate == "country":
                country_obj = object_
                properties.append(f"is located in {country_obj}")
            elif predicate == "capital":
                if "is located in" in properties:
                    country_index = properties.index(f"is located in {country_obj}")
                    properties[country_index] = f"is located in {country_obj}, which has a capital of {object_}."
                else:
                    properties.append(f"has a capital city of {object_}")
```
Rationale:

The original code used "where the capital is" which sounds a bit abrupt. Replacing it with "which has a capital of" sounds more natural. Also, changing "is in" to "is located in" and "has a capital of" to "has a capital city of" improves the phrasing. This aims to improve fluency and potentially the BLEU score by generating sentences closer to the reference sentences. These changes are focused on improving the sentence structure related to location-based triples, which were identified as a weakness in previous evaluations.
Please fix it to the correct format.
